SIMPLE: revolute
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Revolute
<hw>Rev"o*lute</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>revolutus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>revolvere</ets>. See
<er>Revolve</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Rolled backward
or downward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A <xex>revolute</xex> leaf is coiled downwards, with the
lower surface inside the coil. A leaf with <xex>revolute</xex> margins
has the edges rolled under, as in the <xex>Andromeda
polifilia</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revolution</ent>⟦br⟧
